<subSubSection id="48D355CA8ED7FF5A48A75193FE0CFE04" lastPageId="154" lastPageNumber="155" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418ED7FF5948A75193FEBCF927" blockId="153.[151,1437,151,2035]" box="[151,281,1727,1751]" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48ED7FF5948905193FEB5F927" box="[160,272,1727,1751]" captionStart="PLATE 40" captionStartId="156.[151,233,1895,1918]" captionTargetBox="[177,1408,285,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-138@156.[166,1421,255,1918]" captionText="PLATE 40. A–C. Male genitalia. D, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Anteon pilosum, holotype (from Xu et al. 2010b). B. A. priscum, paratype (proximal membranous process removed) (from Olmi 1991). C. A. priscum from China, Ningxia. D. A. provinciale (from Olmi 1991). E. A. pteromaculatum (from Xu et al. 2011d). Scale bar 0.22 mm for A, 0.10 mm for B and C, 0.16 mm for D, 0.35 mm for E" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412460/files/figure.png" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">Plate 40A</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418ED7FF5948A75024FCCDF8EE" blockId="153.[151,1437,151,2035]" box="[151,872,1800,1822]" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">
Anteon pilosum Xu, Olmi &amp; He 2010b: 18; Xu et al. 
<quantity id="C731ABA48ED7FF594A815024FD4AF8EE" box="[689,751,1800,1822]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.011" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" unit="g" value="2011.0">2011g</quantity>
(Suppl.): 9.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418ED7FF5A48A75066FE0CFE04" blockId="153.[151,1437,151,2035]" lastBlockId="154.[151,1437,151,824]" lastPageId="154" lastPageNumber="155" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">
Description of Male. Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48ED7FF594A945066FC97F892" box="[676,818,1866,1890]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.55" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="153" pageNumber="154" unit="mm" value="3.55" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.9 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38ED7FF5948A75042FF5CF876" box="[151,249,1902,1926]" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">holotype</typeStatus>
with segment 1 testaceous and rest of antenna brown, except ventral side testaceous; antenna of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38ED7FF594D0C5043FA39F877" box="[1340,1436,1903,1927]" pageId="153" pageNumber="154">paratype</typeStatus>
with dorsal side brown and ventral side testaceous; mesosoma black; metasoma brown; legs testaceous, except proand mesocoxa partly brown and metacoxa almost completely brown. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 11:7:11:11:10:10:8:10:9:13. Head shiny, smooth, punctate, unsculptured among punctures; face with two lateral longitudinal keels near orbits directed towards antennal toruli; frontal line incomplete, only shortly present in front of anterior ocellus; occipital carina complete; POL = 8; OL = 4; OOL = 8; OPL = 6; TL = 6; greatest breadth of posterior ocelli shorter than OL (3:4). Scutum, scutellum and metanotum shiny, smooth, punctate, unsculptured among punctures. Notauli incomplete, reaching approximately 0.7 length of scutum. Propodeum with strong transverse keel between dorsal and posterior surface; dorsal surface reticulate rugose; posterior surface with two complete longitudinal keels, lateral areas reticulate rugose and median area shiny and smooth. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands; distal part of stigmal vein much shorter than proximal part (3.5:12). Paramere (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48ED4FF5A498156B8FD87FE5C" box="[433,546,404,428]" captionStart="PLATE 40" captionStartId="156.[151,233,1895,1918]" captionTargetBox="[177,1408,285,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-138@156.[166,1421,255,1918]" captionText="PLATE 40. A–C. Male genitalia. D, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Anteon pilosum, holotype (from Xu et al. 2010b). B. A. priscum, paratype (proximal membranous process removed) (from Olmi 1991). C. A. priscum from China, Ningxia. D. A. provinciale (from Olmi 1991). E. A. pteromaculatum (from Xu et al. 2011d). Scale bar 0.22 mm for A, 0.10 mm for B and C, 0.16 mm for D, 0.35 mm for E" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412460" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412460/files/figure.png" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Plate 40A</figureCitation>
) without distal inner pointed or rounded process, with proximal membranous process slightly shorter than volsella and with inner margin provided of numerous hairs. Tibial spurs 1/1/2. Female. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
